# MODE TRANSITIONS: PREFLIGHT & QA GATES

> **TL;DR:** This component handles mode transition gates. Preflight validation gates BUILD mode for L3+ tasks. QA semantic review gates REFLECT mode for L2+ tasks.

## 🔒 BUILD MODE PREVENTION MECHANISM (L3+)

For Level 3+ tasks, the system prevents moving to BUILD mode without passing preflight validation:

```mermaid
graph TD
    Start["User Types: /build"] --> CheckLevel{"Complexity<br>Level?"}
    CheckLevel -->|"Level 1-2"| AllowBuild["Allow BUILD Mode"]
    CheckLevel -->|"Level 3-4"| CheckPreflight{"Preflight<br>Validation Passed?"}
    CheckPreflight -->|"Yes (PASS/ADVISORY)"| AllowBuild
    CheckPreflight -->|"No or Not Run"| BlockBuild["BLOCK BUILD MODE"]
    BlockBuild --> Message["Display:<br>⚠️ PREFLIGHT VALIDATION REQUIRED"]
    Message --> ReturnToPreflight["Prompt: Type /preflight"]

    style CheckLevel fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style CheckPreflight fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style BlockBuild fill:#ff0000,stroke:#990000,color:white,stroke-width:3px
    style Message fill:#ff5555,stroke:#dd3333,color:white
    style ReturnToPreflight fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
```

### Preflight Status Check
The system checks `memory-bank/.preflight_status` before allowing BUILD mode for L3+ tasks:
- **PASS** or **ADVISORY**: Allow transition to BUILD mode
- **FAIL** or missing: Block BUILD mode, prompt `/preflight`

## 🔒 REFLECT MODE PREVENTION MECHANISM (L2+)

For Level 2+ tasks, the system prevents moving to REFLECT mode without passing QA review:

```mermaid
graph TD
    Start["User Types: /reflect"] --> CheckLevel{"Complexity<br>Level?"}
    CheckLevel -->|"Level 1"| AllowReflect["Allow REFLECT Mode"]
    CheckLevel -->|"Level 2-4"| CheckQA{"QA Validation<br>Passed?"}
    CheckQA -->|"Yes"| AllowReflect
    CheckQA -->|"No or Not Run"| BlockReflect["BLOCK REFLECT MODE"]
    BlockReflect --> Message["Display:<br>⚠️ QA REVIEW REQUIRED"]
    Message --> ReturnToQA["Prompt: Type /qa"]

    style CheckLevel fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style CheckQA fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style BlockReflect fill:#ff0000,stroke:#990000,color:white,stroke-width:3px
    style Message fill:#ff5555,stroke:#dd3333,color:white
    style ReturnToQA fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
```

### QA Status Check
The system checks `memory-bank/.qa_validation_status` before allowing REFLECT mode for L2+ tasks:
- **PASS**: Allow transition to REFLECT mode
- **FAIL** or missing: Block REFLECT mode, prompt `/qa`

## 🚨 MODE TRANSITION TRIGGERS

### CREATIVE to PREFLIGHT Transition (L3+):
After completing the CREATIVE phase:
```
⏭️ NEXT MODE: /preflight
To validate the implementation plan before building, please type '/preflight'
```

### PREFLIGHT to BUILD Transition (On Success):
After successful preflight validation:
```
✅ PREFLIGHT VALIDATION COMPLETE
Plan validated against codebase reality
You may now proceed to BUILD mode
Type '/build' to begin implementation
```

### BUILD to QA Transition (L2+):
After completing implementation:
```
⏭️ NEXT MODE: /qa
To perform post-build semantic review, please type '/qa'
```

### QA to REFLECT Transition (On Success):
After successful QA review:
```
✅ QA REVIEW COMPLETE
All semantic checks passed
You may now proceed to REFLECT mode
Type '/reflect' to begin reflection
```

**Next Step (on PREFLIGHT PASS):** Continue to BUILD mode.
**Next Step (on PREFLIGHT FAIL):** Return to `/plan` or fix and re-run `/preflight`.
**Next Step (on QA PASS):** Continue to REFLECT mode.
**Next Step (on QA FAIL):** Return to `/build` or `/plan` depending on severity.
